light, and X, gamma, and cosmic rays. Each of these constitutes a portion of the \\textbf{electromagnetic spectrum}. Not all portions of the spectrum are currently usable for telecommunications, however. The media to harness those that are usable are also limited to a few types.

In telecommunications, transmission media can be divided into two broad categories: guided and unguided. Guided media include twisted-pair cable, coaxial cable, and fiber-optic cable. Unguided medium is free space. Figure 7.2 shows this taxonomy.

\\textbf{Figure 7.2} \\textit{Classes of transmission media}

