\\subsection{Coaxial Cable Connectors}
To connect coaxial cable to devices, we need coaxial connectors. The most common type of connector used today is the \\textbf{Bayonet Neill-Concelman (BNC)} connector. Figure~\\ref{fig:bnc_connectors} shows three popular types of these connectors: the BNC connector, the BNC T connector, and the BNC terminator.

