\\subsubsection{Multipoint Network}
A multipoint network uses ADMs to allow communications between several terminals. An ADM removes the signal belonging to the terminal connected to it and adds the signal transmitted from another terminal. Each terminal can send data to one or more downstream terminals. Figure 14.32 shows a unidirectional scheme in which each terminal can send data only to the downstream terminals, but a multipoint network can be bidirectional, too.

