\\subsection{17.1 CONNECTING DEVICES}
Hosts and networks do not normally operate in isolation. We use \\textit{connecting devices} to connect hosts together to make a network or to connect networks together to make an internet. Connecting devices can operate in different layers of the Internet model. We discuss three kinds of \\textit{connecting devices}: hubs, link-layer switches, and routers. Hubs today operate in the first layer of the Internet model. Link-layer switches operate in the first two layers. Routers operate in the first three layers. (See Figure 17.1.)

