\\node (receiver_ready) [rectangle, draw, fill=blue!20, below of=receiver_start] {Ready};
\\node (receiver_corrupt) [rectangle, draw, fill=white, left of=receiver_ready, xshift=-2cm] {Corrupted packet arrived.\\\\Discard the packet.};
\\node (receiver_outside) [rectangle, draw, fill=white, right of=receiver_ready, xshift=2cm] {Error-free packet with seqNo outside window boundaries arrived.\\\\Discard the packet.\\\\Send an ACK with ackNo = $R_n$.};
\\node (receiver_inside) [rectangle, draw, fill=white, above of=receiver_ready, yshift=1.5cm] {Error-free packet with seqNo inside window arrived.\\\\If duplicate, discard; otherwise, store the packet.\\\\Send an ACK with ackNo = seqNo.\\\\If seqNo = $R_n$, deliver the packet and all previously arrived and stored packets to application, and slide window.};

\\draw[->] (receiver_start) -- (receiver_ready);
\\draw[->] (receiver_ready) -- node[anchor=east] {Corrupted packet arrived.\\\\Discard the packet.} (receiver_corrupt);
\\draw[->] (receiver_corrupt) -- (receiver_ready);
\\draw[->] (receiver_ready) -- node[anchor=east] {Error-free packet with seqNo outside window boundaries arrived.\\\\Discard the packet.\\\\Send an ACK with ackNo = $R_n$.} (receiver_outside);
\\draw[->] (receiver_outside) -- (receiver_ready);
\\draw[->] (receiver_ready) -- node[anchor=east] {Error-free packet with seqNo inside window arrived.\\\\If duplicate, discard; otherwise, store the packet.\\\\Send an ACK with ackNo = seqNo.\\\\If seqNo = $R_n$, deliver the packet and all previously arrived and stored packets to application, and slide window.} (receiver_inside);
\\draw[->] (receiver_inside) -- (receiver_ready);
\\end{tikzpicture}
\\end{center}

\\textbf{Note:} All arithmetic equations are in modulo $2^m$.

\\textbf{a.} If an error-free packet with seqNo in the window arrives, the packet is stored and an ACK with ackNo = seqNo is sent. In addition, if the seqNo = $R_n$, then the packet and all previously arrived consecutive packets are delivered to the application layer and the window slides so that the $R_n$ points to the first empty slot.

\\textbf{b.} If an error-free packet with seqNo outside the window arrives, the packet is discarded, but an ACK with ackNo = $R_n$ is returned to the sender. This is needed to let the sender slide its window if some ACKs related to packets with seqNo < $R_n$ were lost.

\\textbf{c.} If a corrupted packet arrives, the packet is discarded.

