address constructed in lines 18 to 21. Lines 35 to 39 are new in TCP communication.
The listen function is called to let the operating system complete the connection
establishment phase and put the clients in the waiting list. Lines 44 to 48 call the accept
function to remove the next client in the waiting list and start serving it. This function
blocks if there is no client in the waiting list. Lines 50 to 56 code the data transfer sec-
tion depicted in Figure 25.13. The maximum buffer size, the length of the string echoed, is the same as shown in Figure 25.14.
