\\subsection{Fourth Approach: Using a Media Server and RTSP}
The \\textbf{Real-Time Streaming Protocol (RTSP)} is a control protocol designed to add more functionalities to the streaming process. Using RTSP, we can control the playing of audio/video. RTSP is an out-of-band control protocol that is similar to the second connection in FTP. Figure 28.27 shows a media server and RTSP.

