\\subsection{Protocols}
H.323 uses a number of protocols to establish and maintain voice (or video) communication. Figure~\\ref{fig:h323-protocols} shows some of these protocols. H.323 uses G.71 or G.723.1 for compression. It uses a protocol named H.245, which allows the parties to negotiate the compression method. Protocol Q.931 is used for establishing and terminating connections. Another protocol, called H.225, or Registration/Administration/Status (RAS), is used for registration with the gatekeeper.

